Let's think step by step and use knowledge in similar problem to solve this problem

First, we notice that $M+M$ in the ones place must be a two-digit number, so we carry over the one to the tens place. This gives us the following addition problem:

\[
\begin{array}{@{}c@{\;}c@{}c@{}c@{}c}
& & G & M & M \\
+ & & G & M & \\
\cline{2-5}
& E & G & M & M \\
\end{array}
\]

