& & G & 5 & 5 \\
+ & & G & 5 & \\
\cline{2-5}
& E & G & 5 & 5 \\
\end{array}
\]

Since $G+G$ in the ones place is an even number, we know that $G$ is either 4 or 6. However, $G$ cannot be 4 because then $E$ would be 9, which is not allowed since each letter represents a distinct digit. Therefore, $G=6$.

Now we have the following addition problem:

\[
